Q1 Part 1:

Command: whoami
Output:  kartik
Command: groups
Output:  adm cdrom sudo dip plugdev users lpadmin

Explanation:'whoami' displays the current username. 'groups' lists all the groups that this user belong to

Q1 Part 2:

Command: pwd
Output: /home/kartik
Command: ls -la
Output: total 80 ( In the Screenshot)

Explanation: 'pwd' shows the present working directory. 'ls -la' lists all the files in the current directory inluding the hidden files in a long format showing detailed attributes.

Q1 Part 3: 

Command: echo "Linux user environment verified" > user_info.txt
Command: cat user_info.txt
Output: Linux user environment verified

Explanation: 'echo "Linux user environment verified" > user_info.txt' creates a new file user_info.txt with "Linux user environment verified" as text. 'cat user_info.txt' displays the contents of the file user_info.txt

Q1 Part 4: 

Command: wc -m user_info.txt
Output: 32 user_info.txt

Explanation: 'wc -m' counts the number of characters in a file. output shows 32 characters which includes the newline character also.

Q1 Part 5:

Command: man mkdir
Command: ls
Command: mkdir -p dir1/dir2
Command: ls
Command: cd dir1
Command: ls
Output: In Screenshot

Explanation: "mkdir -p' helps to create parent directory and nested directory in one command. 'ls' lists all the files in the current directory. 'mkdir -p dir1/dir2' creates nested directory with dir1 as parent directory. 'cd dir1' moves us to dir1.

Q1 Part 6: 

Command: ls ~ | sort
Output: In Screenshot

Explanation: Displays all the files and folder in the home directory in the alphabetical order

Q1 Part 7: 

Command: grep "admin" log.txt
Command: echo -e "admin login successful\nuser login failed\nadmin logout" > log.txt
Output: admin login successful
        admin logout

Explanation: log.txt file didn't exist so created a file log.txt and 'echo -e' to print the text in the file and -e for using escape sequences \n

Q1 Part 8:

Command: uname -r
Output: 6.14.0.37-generic

Explanation: Displays the current kernel verison that is working on the system

Q1 Part 9:

Command: ping -c 5 www.google.com
Output: In the screenshot

Explanation: 5 ICMP packets were sent to www.google.com 0% packet loss confirms active internet connection.

Q1 Part 10: 

Command: uptime
Output: 13:22:06 up 24min, 1 user, load average: 0.00, 0.02, 0.06

Explanation: System is running from 24min and 1 user is logged in. average load for last 1min, 5min, 15mins is 0.00, 0.02, 0.06 respectively. 
